description: Baking coves line the eastern walls of the kitchen above three hearths, two of which are banked for the night, while a third houses the morning's porridge.  Several bakers work white-washed preparation tables, kneading and mixing the next day's bread as they quietly converse.  Neatly dividing the cooking area from the dining room is a bird's-eye maple serving table with several dishes still upon it for late night visitors.

Baking coves line the eastern walls of the kitchen above three hearths, three of which are roasting meats for the evening meal, while the third houses the morning's porridge.  Neatly dividing the cooking area from the dining room is a bird's-eye maple serving table with several dishes arranged for easy serving.
title: [Sunfist Outpost, Kitchen]
